<br>
What 3D is doing is trying to head off the inevitable nerf bat that is already preparing to swing in the general direction of the assassin classes.<br>
<br>
It's like the video game industry - see all those warning labels?  It was do it themselves or have it enforced by a govt agency.  Guess which one is better for the game-makers? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Very recently a series of duels were done between a L50 infil and L50 warrior.  Both among the most experienced players of their classes in the game.<br>
<br>
The infil won 3/4 of all the duels.  That was when the warrior KNEW the infil was coming for him.  The fact is that right now a solo assassin can take out almost any class in the game - if they are solo.  That's not the way the class is designed.<br>
<br>
3D recognizes this, and has seen that the nerfbat is incoming.  He'd rather see some self-regulation done, with specific hits that are a bit controlled.<br>
<br>
The two areas that are overpowering assassins are PA and envenom.  Do you really want to see both those abilities denuded?  Or would you rather see some controlled actions taken to remove the specific issues that are creating overpowered assassins?<br>
