There are far better ways than this to come up with fixes.  In my opinion, envenom needs to be fixed, stealth needs tweaks, SBs may need looked at for their damage caps, but using 3dknight's test with Origen is 'not the way' to look at CS critical hit damage.  If a mouse takes enough bites out of the cat he'll win.  Even with 3dknight's PA and run method, collision would solve it, and intercept on a caster would keep the caster from getting killed.  Deciding HE knows that removing the extremely rare already critical hits on CS styles is the best thing, is NOT correct.  Btw, I don't call 42 in envenom &quot;substandard&quot;, not by a long shot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=majin>Majin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/02 6:08:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2766.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reply</span><hr size=1> Mh, about this &quot;run technique&quot; abuse...i dont get - so you say if i run towards a target - or the target run towards me and i PA him its an abuse of a design flaw ? How ? I always done it like that way - its very difficult to PA someone running towards you because of lag and such... how is this an abuse ? <p><img border=0 src=http://members.tripod.de/majin_mlf/midgard_ownz_small.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukevintest.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kevintest</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Register