<br>
Not sure which it should be - with people already speccing based on env items giving new poisons, I'd suggest just give the other classes the same benefit, maybe.<br>
<br>
Nerfing stealth in any way would pretty much shut down both the minstrel and infiltrator - both of which (assuming stealth minstrel template) rely on stealth to get them &quot;up close and personal&quot; with their opponent.  You basically can't reduce stealth's effectiveness without really hurting those classes.<br>
<br>
Damage caps in general have to be set up so that the one-shot kill POSSIBILITY is removed.  I know that CS hits don't crit often (and it's mostly the 800 pt infil hits and 1000+ SB hits that get the bad PR and the blood boiling).  You know it.  But the player who gets hit ONE TIME by a hit like that does not.  He figures it will happen &quot;every time&quot;.  And he tells his friends, who tell their friends, etc.<br>
<br>
Fact is that one-shot kills (or kills that occur so fast that there is no time or chance to react in any way) between even cons are bad for the game.  They discourage people from trying to play, and reduce the level of skill by increasing the luck factor.<br>
<br>
Personally, my thought is that CS crits are so darn uncommon anyway that it really hurts the class exactly ZERO to remove 'em.  Leave standard CS damage alone.  But remove the wild, crazy, radical damage spikes.  From caster bolts too - they are just as bad.  One thousand point bolts should NEVER be happening.  My opinion. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The only other solution is to base caster defense abilities off the high spikes of damage - which is what will likely happen otherwise.  Casters will be designed to survive 800pt CS +400pt poison strikes...  So unbuffed they'd need around 900-1000hp, or about 300 more than they get now, or maybe a bigger absorb buff.  That's a _bad_ solution though, really - because it bases the whole on the extreme hits, and thus reduces assassin effectiveness on the standard, everyday hits.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong - casters are SUPPOSED to die to assassins, almost every fight.  And they do.  Usually so fast they don't have time to blink. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   The loss vs assassins should stay - the &quot;can't blink&quot; should not.<br>
<br>
Which reminds me - yes, an assassin should die vs a tank, about as often as a caster dies to an assassin.  3D's best win % vs a L50 warrior should have been maybe 5-10%.  Not 75%.  Tanks are the &quot;predator&quot; class for assassins - and are supposed to kill them with GREAT consistancy, if they find them.  And yes, he used specialized tactics - but now that Khel has so kindly published them, so can everyone else.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   No, collision is not a solution, because it's an equine lich.  Unfortunately.<br>
<br>
And 42 env with items really IS low for an infiltrator now, Khel - or should be.  A better term for 3D's template would have been &quot;suboptimal&quot;, not &quot;substandard&quot; - since it was nowhere near an optimal template for the style of fighting he was doing.  Would have been much easier in those fights if he had gone to 50 env buffed.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
If you do the math - and assume that you are trying for a template that can &quot;kite-kill&quot; effectively - then the poison skill is actually even more important than the CS skill - and is VERY, VERY much more important than thrust.  51 buffed thrust and only 42 buffed envenom?  =P  Fifty buffed envenom is now optimal in general, btw - with the new poison buff, and the new Env items, that is NOT hard to get and VERY worth it.  IMHO.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
***  All of the above is the personal opinion of me as a player.  I have played every class in Albion to a decent level (mid+) during the course of the last 15 months of playing DAOC, so I have a decent basis on which to compare the way they play.  However - none of this should be construed as anything but the ramblings of someone bored at work.  They are ideas, and not official in any way.  I don't have a hidden agenda to demolish the Infiltrator - rather the contrary, because I enjoy playing the class.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
***  I am not &quot;sticking up&quot; for 3D's ideas, or posting against them.  I am suggesting that crucifying the guy for doing his best is probably pretty stupid.  And that flamefests directed at people who are asking for opinions and comments are pretty dumb too.  If a TL comes to the public boards (which they are never, ever required to do) to put out ideas and seek feedback, burning them at the stake is a surefire way to ensure that next time, they just make their suggestions to Mythic without asking for the comments.<br>
<br>
Kevin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukevintest.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kevintest</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/02 6:21:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2766.topic&index=32>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reply</span><hr size=1> Majin, what he's talking about is PAing the target, then running THROUGH them, and past, so they get no counter-attack.  Then you run off while they are trying to turn around, and you stealth.  It's possible to use said technique to kite targets that are MUCH tougher than you'd ordinarily be able to kill.<br>
